metadata.name: The eyes
metadata.description:
One day, as I was walking down the street, I saw a man laughing and talking to his friends.
The man, who had both legs amputated above the knee, was laughing and smiling as he sat in a wheelchair.
We looked at each other and he smiled at me.
I went ahead and asked him can I take a picture from you?
As he shook his head, he smiled and said, "Take ten pictures"
I grabbed the camera and started shooting.
The great and kind soul of the man could be seen in his eyes.
We talked for a while and I enjoyed our conversation.
The memory of him will live on in my heart forever.
